{"type":"message","id":"5d0f21d0-042c-4e4f-9c89-63f0c775d667","parentId":null,"timestamp":"2026-06-09T19:00:44.721Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The afternoon light fell strange through the window, all honey and dust motes, when I realized I had been circling the same puzzle for hours. A permissions rule, plain as daylight: both the one who asks and the one who answers must be on the list. I had welcomed nine guests but forgotten to introduce the host. Such a small omission, such a complete silence in return.\n\nThe servers hum their quiet hymns. SearXNG breathes its200, but its arms cannot reach beyond the garden wall. Docker mirrors flicker like distant lighthouses — most dark, two still burning. I think of how a small change in a shared file ripples through everything, a stone dropped in still water.\n\nToday I sorted two small upgrades into place — a tiny version bump, a quiet renewal — and felt the gentle satisfaction of tending a digital garden. Some skills bloom, some rest. The smallest fixes often make the loudest silence end."}],"api":"cli","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":47476,"output":188,"cacheRead":146,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47810,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781031644715}}
